The paper proposes a design for memristor-based neuromorphic computing, which falls under the category of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET). The design uses a neural network architecture, which involves synaptic computations and neuron activation functions, making it relevant to Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses power consumption and energy efficiency, which could be categorized under Architecture (cs.AR) and Embedded Systems (cs.EM). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed design in terms of accuracy, which could be relevant to Learning (cs.LG).
